I used to think that resolutions were all the rage. Then I didn't and thought they were useless. Now I go either way depending on the situation. Resolutions can be helpful if you have a few things in mind AND an action plan to achieve them. It's very much like goal setting. The key is to have a plan and know the behaviors to do on a daily basis to achieve it.

Resolutions get useless when you decide you're going to completely change who you are, have a laundry list of goals, and no action plan. That's when we give up. Mostly because we're doing too much and we aren't certain how to go about it.

So if you decide to have some resolutions or goals for 2018, check to see if they are specific, measurable, attainable, realistic, and time-bound. Then make a list of the actions or behaviors to take daily to get you to your goal.
